The paper discusses a novel topology for end-to-end speech recognition using recurrent neural networks. This falls under the sub-category of natural language processing (NLP) and speech recognition (SD) in computer science. Additionally, the paper also discusses the use of convolutional neural networks (CV) for feature extraction and classification, and the optimization of the network using gradient descent (NE). Therefore, the likely arXiv CS sub-categories are cs.SD, cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.NE, and cs.CV, in order of most to least likely.
